items.body:
🟡 **Ambiguous optional fields** — `CodeBasedEvaluatorDefinition` previously required `code_text: string`. This PR makes it optional and adds three new optional fields (`entry_point`, `image_tag`, `blob_uri`), creating an interface where all four alternatives are optional with no way for callers to know which combination is valid:

```ts
export interface CodeBasedEvaluatorDefinition extends EvaluatorDefinition {
    blob_uri?: string;
    code_text?: string;       // was required before
    entry_point?: string;
    image_tag?: string;
    type: "code";
}
```

A discriminated union would better express mutually exclusive modes (e.g., inline code vs. blob-uploaded code):
```ts
type CodeBasedEvaluatorDefinition =
  | { type: "code"; code_text: string; ... }
  | { type: "code"; blob_uri: string; entry_point: string; image_tag: string; ... };
```

If a union is not feasible due to codegen constraints, at minimum document which field combinations are valid.
